<TEXT>
 airlines must tell consumers who ask for the lowest fares that the best deals
 may be available on their internet sites.
 the transportation department issued the reminder <TIMEX2 val="2000-10-20" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">yesterday</TIMEX2> as it rejected an
 industry request for new rules.
 federal law prohibits airlines from deceiving consumers about prices.
 according to the d.o.t., an airline is violating federal law if it does not
 alert customers to online deals.
